# GoArrive — Windsurf Rules

## Project
GoArrive is an online fitness coaching platform. React Native + Expo + Expo Router + Firebase. Single codebase for web, iOS, Android. Multi-tenant, three roles: platformAdmin, coach, member.

## Stack
React Native, Expo, Expo Router, TypeScript (strict), Cloud Firestore, Firebase Auth, Cloud Functions Gen 2, Firebase Hosting, Stripe Connect, Zoom API, Google Calendar API.
NO MySQL, TiDB, Drizzle, Fastify, or S3.

## Critical Auth Pattern
Always use `effectiveUid` or `claims.coachId` from `useAuth()` — never `user.uid`.
All coach-scoped queries must include `where('coachId', '==', coachId)`.
This is required for admin impersonation to work.

## Code Style
- camelCase: Firestore documents, TypeScript interfaces, props, state
- "coach" not trainer, "member" not client, "movement" not exercise, "Command Center" not dashboard
- FlatList for lists > 500 items
- thumbnailUrl for initial media loads
- Soft deletes via isArchived, never hard deletes

## Roles
Three roles only: platformAdmin, coach, member. No fourth role.

## Build Tab
Workout creation starts on a blank block canvas, not a form.
Movements use 4:5 aspect ratio.

## Testing & Deployment
- Vitest: `cd apps/goarrive && npm run test:vitest`
- Playwright: `npm run test:e2e`
- Always deploy to staging first: `cd apps/goarrive && npm run deploy:staging`
- Never deploy to production without explicit approval

## Do Not Build
MySQL, TiDB, Drizzle, S3, Fastify, JotForm, Calendly, Zoom Embedded SDK, additional roles, white-label.

